(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on turning rough notes into a coherent paragraph.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in clarity, organization, sentence control, and audience) Tj
T*
(awareness that the question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Writing step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on guided composition and editing.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
(3. Point out how to avoid writing without planning or revising while solving it.) Tj
T*
(4. Review the result and connect it back to the topic overview.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Common Mistakes) Tj
T*
(- Misunderstanding the core focus of Writing: clarity, organization, sentence control,) Tj
T*
(and audience awareness.) Tj
T*
(- Writing without planning or revising.) Tj
T*
(- Jumping to an answer without showing the steps or reasoning clearly.) Tj
T*
(- Practising Writing without checking whether the method matches the question being) Tj
T*
(asked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Study Tips) Tj
T*
(- Rewrite the overview of Writing in your own words after studying it.) Tj
T*
(- Use short exercises built around guided composition and editing before trying harder) Tj
T*
(tasks.) Tj
T*
(- Keep track of mistakes such as writing without planning or revising and write the) Tj
T*
(correction beside each one.) Tj
T*
(- Revise Writing regularly so the method behind clarity, organization, sentence control,) Tj
T*
(and audience awareness becomes familiar.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Practice Exercises) Tj
T*
(- Explain the overview of Writing and describe how it fits into English.) Tj
T*
(- Work through an example based on turning rough notes into a coherent paragraph and) Tj
T*
(explain each step.) Tj
T*
(- Describe why writing without planning or revising causes errors and how to avoid it.) Tj
T*
(- Answer an exam-style question that focuses on guided composition and editing.) Tj
T*
() Tj
